./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:3:description: Review automated pull requests with the `library-bulk-update` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that bumps tested versions for existing libraries, including approve vs close decisions, CI checks, diff-scope validation, and verification of `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `repository-url` changes.
./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:64:   - Review `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, `documentation-url`, and `repository-url` with the same rules used by `PopulateArtifactURLs`.
./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:65:   - For pre-release promotions, verify the `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` values were rendered from the old version to the promoted `metadata-version` or otherwise corrected to an exact-version URL. Do not accept stale URLs that still point at the old pre-release.
./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:75:- `repository-url` is the canonical repository root URL.
./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:76:- `repository-url` must not include a versioned tree path such as `/tree/<tag>`.
./skills/review-library-bulk-update/SKILL.md:77:- `source-code-url`, `test-code-url`, and `documentation-url` must point to the exact library version in the changed entry.
